{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"wood-heedless-sheldrake","description":"# Stage-1 BM25F candidate generation over digests + graph-exclusion filter\n\n## Why\nStage 1 must narrow a few hundred tickets to ~20 candidates cheaply and deterministically, with no LLM and no embeddings, and must NOT surface a ticket's own already-related work (parents/children/siblings/linked) — the top source of \"legitimately related but distinct\" false flags.\n\n## What\n- A brute-force BM25F \"More Like This\" over corpus digests: field-weighted (problem_keywords/component high; propositions/entities lower), with the precision knobs from Lucene MLT prior art — `max_doc_freq` + stopwords to prune project boilerplate, a `minimum_should_match`-style overlap floor. Query side = the query ticket's freshly-extracted digest (S1) built from current full text. Returns top ~20 by score.\n- A graph-exclusion filter applied BEFORE scoring: drop the query ticket's parents, children, siblings (same parent), and any ticket already linked to it by any relation. Reuse the existing dependency/hierarchy reads (`src/rebar/_engine_support/next_batch.py` graph BFS, `ticket_deps`).\n- Skip corpus tickets whose digest is absent/stale (cold-store degrades quietly — no fallback).\n\n## Scope\n- IN scope: the BM25F scorer over digests (pure-Python, brute-force), field weighting, boilerplate pruning, top-K, graph exclusion. OUT: the LLM judge (S6), review-plan wiring (S7).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Given a query digest and corpus digests, returns the top ~K (configurable, default ~20) by field-weighted BM25F score, sub-10ms at a few hundred tickets.\n- [ ] Candidates EXCLUDE the query ticket's parents, children, siblings, and any already-linked tickets.\n- [ ] Corpus tickets with absent/stale digests are skipped (not matched on raw text — no fallback).\n- [ ] Boilerplate terms (high corpus doc-frequency, stopwords, project name) do not drive matches (verified on a fixture with shared boilerplate but distinct work).\n- [ ] Precision knobs (`max_doc_freq`, overlap floor, field weights, K) are configurable.","id":"5a8f-d6a0-ca32-4f51","parent_id":"bd83-c56f-1f72-4ef2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Stage-1 BM25F candidate generation over digests + graph-exclusion filter"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783568205307081001,"uuid":"e2f43a78-95c8-4a90-b9da-354cc065f611"}